{"id":"8671","name":"Create Syslog Entry","tagline":"Creates a Syslog Entry in an specified Logfile","icon":"ios14 c2071128575 g61440","latest":"26094","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>When having long shortcuts, this allows you to create Logfile Entries.</p>\n<h1>Usage Instructions</h1>\n<h2>In the Shortcut File</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a dictionary at the top of your Shortcut with the following Values and Keys:</li>\n<li>logSettings (Type: Dictionary) - Can be named whatever you want</li>\n<li>logSettings.enabled (Optional) (Type: Boolean) - This is only required, if you want to enable Logging from one Place</li>\n<li>logSettings.fileName (Type: Text) - Sets the Name of the File (do NOT add the File Extension). Cannot be Empty. </li>\n<li>logSettings.filePath (Type: Text) - Sets the Path of the File (no need to add trailing or beginning Slashes)</li>\n<li>logSettings.logLevel (Type: Text) - String of the Log Level (more Info below). Cannot be empty. </li>\n<li>logSettings.logScriptName (Optional) (Type: Text) - Optional String to set the Shortcut Name, if you change the Name and do not want to set it in every Log Entry. </li>\n</ol>\n<h2>For each Log Entry</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>If you set logSettings.enabled, create an If loop, which asks for the Boolean of the dictionary value</li>\n<li>Create a Dictionary with the following Keys and Values:</li>\n<li>entryTimestamp (Type: Text) - Current Date in the following Date and Time Format: ISO 8601. Cannot be empty. </li>\n<li>entryLogLevel (Type: Text) - String of the Log Level (more Info below). Cannot be empty. </li>\n<li>entryMessage (Type: Text) - Log Message</li>\n</ol>\n<h1>Further Information</h1>\n<h2>Log Levels</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>0 - DEBUG</li>\n<li>1 - INFO</li>\n<li>2 - WARNING</li>\n<li>3 - ERROR</li>\n<li>4 - CRITICAL</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>ToDo-List</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>There is currently no Item on this ToDo-List</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For further Information just message me: routinehub-feedback@maximilianbaehr.com</p>\n\t\t\t\t","relea